MarketWatch
Other Dow Jones










Smith & Nephew profit rises; on track for targets
LONDON--Smith & Nephew PLC (SN.LN) said Thursday it is on track to achieve its 2017 growth target as it reported a 17% rise in half year pretax profit. The medical technology company's pretax profit during the half year to July 1 rose to $383 million from $327 million a year earlier. Revenue was little changed over the period at $2.34 billion compared with $2.33 billion.

Jul. 27, 2017 at 3:31 a.m. ET
by MarketWatch.com









Smith & Nephew revenue unchanged
LONDON--Smith & Nephew PLC (SN.LN) reported Friday a flat revenue of $1.14 billion, impacted by its Gynaecology business disposal and currency headwinds, but backed its full-year guidance. The company's revenue, however, was strongly supported by the emerging markets, which returned to double digit growth, it said.

May. 5, 2017 at 2:23 a.m. ET
by MarketWatch.com









